---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Research | Jing Betty Feng"
  description="Research themes, selected publications, and scholarly contributions by Jing Betty Feng — spanning AI and organizational behavior, global identity, and innovation pedagogy."
>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-hero__label">Research</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Rigorous Scholarship at the Intersection of Practice and Theory</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__intro">
        Betty's research examines how organizations, individuals, and educational
        institutions adapt to the forces reshaping global business — from AI adoption
        to cultural dynamics in multinational settings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RESEARCH OVERVIEW -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="overview-heading">
    <div class="container container--prose">
      <p class="section-label">Overview</p>
      <h2 id="overview-heading">Research Orientation</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>
      <p>
        Betty's research is characterized by a scholar-practitioner's attention to
        organizational reality. Her work draws on her background in multinational firms
        to formulate research questions that matter beyond the academy — examining
        how global, technological, and cultural forces shape management, learning,
        and institutional life.
      </p>
      <p>
        Her scholarship appears across journals in international business, management
        education, organizational behavior, and innovation. She pursues interdisciplinary
        work that bridges management theory, cross-cultural psychology, educational
        science, and technology studies.
      </p>
      <p>
        Betty is particularly interested in how individuals and organizations make
        sense of disruption — whether that disruption comes from AI, globalization,
        sustainability transitions, or shifting workforce expectations. The connective
        thread across her research is a commitment to understanding learning, adaptation,
        and human agency in complex organizational settings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RESEARCH THEMES -->
  <section class="section section--alt" aria-labelledby="themes-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header--center">
        <p class="section-label">Scholarship</p>
        <h2 id="themes-heading">Research Themes</h2>
        <p class="section-intro text-center" style="margin-inline:auto;">
          Betty's work is organized around three intersecting themes — each grounded
          in organizational realities she has observed directly and examined rigorously.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="themes">
        <div class="theme-block">
          <div class="theme-block__header">
            <span class="theme-block__num">01</span>
            <h3 class="theme-block__title">AI, Learning, and Organizational Behavior</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="theme-block__body">
            How do individuals and organizations learn in the presence of AI?
            Betty's work in this area examines behavioral and managerial
            responses to AI adoption — including how individuals make sense of algorithmic
            decision-making and navigate human-AI collaboration, and how
            business schools should respond to the challenge of educating AI-ready professionals.
          </p>
          <div class="theme-block__examples">
            <p class="theme-examples-label">Related work includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>AI literacy and its impact on learning </li>
              <li>Human-AI teaming: trust, attribution, and role redefinition</li>
              <li>Curriculum design for AI literacy in business education</li>
              <li>SUNY AI for Public Good fellowship research</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="theme-block">
          <div class="theme-block__header">
            <span class="theme-block__num">02</span>
            <h3 class="theme-block__title">Global Identity, Culture, and International Business</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="theme-block__body">
            Betty's most established research stream examines how culture, identity,
            and national context shape organizational behavior in multinational settings.
            Her work draws on psychological and sociological frameworks to interrogate
            the human dimensions of global business strategy — from cross-cultural
            negotiation dynamics to the identity challenges facing managers and 
            bi-cultural professionals.
          </p>
          <div class="theme-block__examples">
            <p class="theme-examples-label">Related work includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>National identity and behavior in MNE contexts</li>
              <li>Cross-cultural negotiation styles and outcomes</li>
              <li>Acculturation and identity in international assignments</li>
              <li>Cultural distance and organizational performance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="theme-block">
          <div class="theme-block__header">
            <span class="theme-block__num">03</span>
            <h3 class="theme-block__title">Innovation, Pedagogy, and Experiential Learning</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="theme-block__body">
            How do innovative pedagogical approaches — design thinking, entrepreneurship
            challenges, experiential simulations — develop practical and disciplinary
            understanding in business students? Betty's research in this area examines
            both the design and the outcomes of experiential business education, with
            particular attention to how applied learning methods shape problem-solving
            capability and cross-functional thinking.
          </p>
          <div class="theme-block__examples">
            <p class="theme-examples-label">Related work includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Innovation Challenge program outcomes and design</li>
              <li>Entrepreneurship education and student self-efficacy</li>
              <li>LEGO Serious Play and facilitation-based learning</li>
              <li>Experiential learning transfer to professional practice</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SELECTED PUBLICATIONS -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="pubs-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Scholarship</p>
        <h2 id="pubs-heading">Selected Publications</h2>
        <div class="section-divider"></div>
        <p class="section-intro">
          A representative selection of Betty's peer-reviewed work.
          Full publication list is available in the <a href="/cv">downloadable CV</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pub-list">
        <div class="pub-item">
          <h3 class="pub-item__title">
            Navigating AI Integration: Sensemaking and identity of human
          </h3>
          <p class="pub-item__meta">
            Journal of International Business Studies &nbsp;·&nbsp; Under Review
          </p>
          <p class="pub-item__note">
            Examines how managers in multinational contexts make sense of AI
            adoption decisions and develop organizational learning responses
            to technology-driven disruption.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pub-item">
          <h3 class="pub-item__title">
            Cultural Distance and Negotiation Outcomes: Evidence from
            Cross-Border Business Interactions
          </h3>
          <p class="pub-item__meta">
            International Business Review &nbsp;·&nbsp; Published
          </p>
          <p class="pub-item__note">
            Empirical study of how cultural distance influences negotiation
            dynamics, trust-building, and deal outcomes in international business settings.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pub-item">
          <h3 class="pub-item__title">
            Identity Salience and Behavior in Multinational Enterprises:
            A Cross-National Comparative Study
          </h3>
          <p class="pub-item__meta">
            Journal of World Business &nbsp;·&nbsp; Published
          </p>
          <p class="pub-item__note">
            Investigates how national identity salience shapes employee behavior,
            organizational commitment, and performance in MNE subsidiaries.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pub-item">
          <h3 class="pub-item__title">
            Designing for Disruption: An Experiential Approach to
            Entrepreneurship Education in Business Schools
          </h3>
          <p class="pub-item__meta">
            Journal of Management Education &nbsp;·&nbsp; Published
          </p>
          <p class="pub-item__note">
            Describes and evaluates the design of an experiential innovation
            program — including curricular philosophy, implementation, and outcomes
            for student capability development.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pub-item">
          <h3 class="pub-item__title">
            Teaching AI Literacy in the Business Classroom:
            Principles, Practice, and Curriculum Design
          </h3>
          <p class="pub-item__meta">
            Academy of Management Learning &amp; Education &nbsp;·&nbsp; Under Review
          </p>
          <p class="pub-item__note">
            A curriculum design article presenting principles and a prototype
            course for introducing AI literacy to undergraduate business students
            without a technical prerequisite.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="pub-cta-note">
        For a complete list of publications, conference presentations, and
        working papers, please <a href="/cv">download the full CV</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONFERENCES -->
  <section class="section section--alt" aria-labelledby="conf-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Scholarly Presentations</p>
        <h2 id="conf-heading">Conferences &amp; Presentations</h2>
        <div class="section-divider"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="conf-grid">
        <div class="conf-item">
          <span class="conf-item__org">Academy of International Business (AIB)</span>
          <p class="conf-item__desc">Annual conference presenter and session organizer; member of program and service committees.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conf-item">
          <span class="conf-item__org">Academy of Management (AoM)</span>
          <p class="conf-item__desc">Presentations in international management, organizational behavior, and management education divisions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conf-item">
          <span class="conf-item__org">Academy of Management Learning &amp; Education</span>
          <p class="conf-item__desc">Presenter on experiential learning, curriculum design, and AI in business education.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conf-item">
          <span class="conf-item__org">SUNY AI for Public Good Symposium</span>
          <p class="conf-item__desc">Fellow presenter on AI literacy, organizational implications, and workforce development.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CURRENT INTERESTS -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="current-heading">
    <div class="container container--prose">
      <p class="section-label">Research Agenda</p>
      <h2 id="current-heading">Current and Emerging Interests</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>
      <p>
        Betty's current research agenda is organized around three emerging areas
        that she expects to define her scholarship in the coming years:
      </p>
      <div class="emerging-list">
        <div class="emerging-item">
          <h3>Generative AI and Organizational Capability</h3>
          <p>
            How do organizations build, deploy, and govern generative AI capabilities —
            and what does this mean for the humans who work alongside these systems?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="emerging-item">
          <h3>Sustainability, Workforce Transitions, and Regional Economies</h3>
          <p>
            As sustainability mandates reshape industries, how do regional
            economies — and the workers within them — navigate transition?
            Betty is exploring this question through partnerships with Long Island
            workforce and sustainability organizations.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="emerging-item">
          <h3>Cross-Cultural Dimensions of Technology Adoption</h3>
          <p>
            How do cultural values and national institutional contexts shape
            the adoption, use, and governance of AI and digital technology
            in multinational organizations?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Themes */
  .themes { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-8); }
  .theme-block {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-10);
  }
  .theme-block__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }
  .theme-block__num {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent-light);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .theme-block__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .theme-block__body {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .theme-block__examples { background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-6); }
  .theme-examples-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .theme-block__examples ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .theme-block__examples li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .theme-block__examples li::before { content: '–'; color: var(--color-gold); flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* Publications */
  .pub-list { margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .pub-cta-note {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  /* Conferences */
  .conf-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-6); }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .conf-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .conf-item {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-6);
  }
  .conf-item__org {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .conf-item__desc { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  /* Emerging */
  .emerging-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-8); margin-top: var(--space-8); }
  .emerging-item {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-gold);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }
  .emerging-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .emerging-item p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
</style>
